data.description: This is a real gem of a property & opportunity! A beautiful corner lot boasting about 10 Live Oak trees with tidal water & the ability to kayak to downtown Charleston if you want to! Seller has never lived in the property (trust sale) however it's a well maintained home with gutters, the roof is approximately 5 years new, windows, doors & hot water heater are newer or replaced. Even with all the trees, the large living room & dining area is bright with beautiful views out back & both have French doors to the deck. 3 bedrooms & 2 baths on one side of the house. The FROG/4th bedrm & full bath are on the other side of the home. The garage was finished to be another bed or living room & full bath. Both of these spaces can be accessed thru the main house or back separate entrance. RiverlandTerrace is a sought after neighborhood with a play park on the water, baseball fields & Riverland Terrace Public Boat Ramp. Conveniently located just five miles from downtown Charleston it's legitimately walkable to a number great restaurants, the Terrace Theater & grocery store & other shops. It's only several miles to the City of Charleston's Municipal Golf Course and in close promimity to Folly Beach.
